# Podium test credentials for the integration and live-test lanes.
#
# Copy this file to test.env (gitignored) and fill in the services you have:
#     cp test.env.example test.env
#
# How it loads:
#   - `make test`, `make test-live`, and `make test-live-external` source it.
#   - `go test ./test/...` loads it through internal/testenv, no make needed.
# Values already in your environment win over this file, so CI keeps its
# injected secrets. Every test self-skips when its variables are absent.
#
# Reading this file: an UNCOMMENTED line is a value you set; a COMMENTED line is
# an optional override with a working default, so leave it commented unless its
# inline note says otherwise.
#
# Not here on purpose: PODIUM_VECTOR_BACKEND, PODIUM_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER, and
# PODIUM_EMBEDDING_MODEL. Those pick a single backend/provider/model for a real
# deployment; the live suites iterate over every backend and provider whose
# credentials are present, so you set credentials, not a selection.


# =============================================================================
# Live-lane switches
# =============================================================================
# Master switch. REQUIRED to run any managed vector or embedding live test.
# PODIUM_LIVE_EXTERNAL=1
# Opt-in marker for the bundled-Dex device-code login e2e (make test-auth-dex).
# PODIUM_LIVE_DEX=1


# =============================================================================
# Local services: Postgres + S3 (docker-compose; `make services-up`)
# =============================================================================
# These match docker-compose.yml. With the services up, the Postgres and S3
# tests take their live path; with them down, they skip.
PODIUM_POSTGRES_DSN=postgres://podium:podium@localhost:5432/podium?sslmode=disable
PODIUM_S3_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9000
PODIUM_S3_BUCKET=podium
PODIUM_S3_REGION=us-east-1
PODIUM_S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=minioadmin
PODIUM_S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=minioadmin
PODIUM_S3_USE_SSL=false
PODIUM_S3_FORCE_PATH_STYLE=true
# Optional: a separate database for the pgvector depth tests. Leave unset to
# reuse PODIUM_POSTGRES_DSN above.
# PODIUM_POSTGRES_DSN_VECTOR=


# =============================================================================
# Managed vector backends (Pinecone, Weaviate Cloud, Qdrant Cloud)
# =============================================================================
# You create the index/collection yourself; the backends do not auto-create one.
# Set only the backends you have. The storage suites need NO embedding-provider
# key (they use a synthetic embedder); self-embedding needs the inference model.
#
# Each backend uses up to two objects:
#
#   1. Storage object: dimension 1536, distance Cosine. The conformance and
#      storage-only suites and the managed semantic-search e2e all share it. The
#      registry supplies the vectors, so 1536-vs-something-else is the only
#      requirement (the synthetic embedder and the conformance suite work at any
#      dimension; 1536 matches the e2e so one object serves both).
#   2. Self-embedding object (optional): a SEPARATE object whose vectors the
#      backend computes from text. It cannot share the storage object, because
#      self-embedding is a different backend configuration (Pinecone Integrated
#      Inference is a different index type; a Weaviate vectorizer class differs
#      from a vectorizer-none class). Create it at the inference model's output
#      dimension (for example multilingual-e5-large = 1024), not 1536.

# ---- Pinecone (app.pinecone.io; free Starter tier) --------------------------
# Storage: create a serverless index, dimension 1536, metric Cosine.
# PODIUM_PINECONE_API_KEY=
# PODIUM_PINECONE_INDEX=podium-test
# Self-embedding (optional): a second index created for an Integrated Inference
# model, plus the model name. Leave both unset to skip the self-embedding test.
# PODIUM_PINECONE_SELFEMBED_INDEX=podium-test-selfembed
# PODIUM_PINECONE_INFERENCE_MODEL=multilingual-e5-large
# Optional overrides (leave unset for the defaults):
# PODIUM_PINECONE_HOST=              # auto-resolved from the index name
# PODIUM_PINECONE_NAMESPACE=         # the test uses its own namespace when unset
# PODIUM_PINECONE_CONTROL_PLANE=     # defaults to https://api.pinecone.io

# ---- Weaviate Cloud (console.weaviate.cloud; Sandbox or Serverless) ---------
# Storage: a collection with vectorizer "none", dimension 1536, distance cosine.
# Auto-schema also creates it on first write.
# PODIUM_WEAVIATE_URL=https://your-cluster.weaviate.cloud
# PODIUM_WEAVIATE_API_KEY=
# PODIUM_WEAVIATE_COLLECTION=PodiumTest
# Self-embedding (optional): a second class configured with a vectorizer module,
# plus that module name. Leave both unset to skip the self-embedding test.
# PODIUM_WEAVIATE_SELFEMBED_COLLECTION=PodiumTestSelfEmbed
# PODIUM_WEAVIATE_VECTORIZER=text2vec-weaviate
# Optional: PODIUM_WEAVIATE_GRPC_URL is reserved and not read; leave unset.

# ---- Qdrant Cloud (cloud.qdrant.io; free 1 GB cluster) ----------------------
# Storage: create a collection with vector size 1536, distance Cosine, e.g.:
#   curl -X PUT "$PODIUM_QDRANT_URL/collections/podium_test" \
#     -H "api-key: $PODIUM_QDRANT_API_KEY" -H 'content-type: application/json' \
#     -d '{"vectors": {"size": 1536, "distance": "Cosine"}}'
# PODIUM_QDRANT_URL=https://your-cluster.cloud.qdrant.io:6333
# PODIUM_QDRANT_API_KEY=
# PODIUM_QDRANT_COLLECTION=podium_test
# Self-embedding (optional): a second collection sized to the inference model's
# dimension, plus the model name. Leave both unset to skip the self-embedding test.
# PODIUM_QDRANT_SELFEMBED_COLLECTION=podium_test_selfembed
# PODIUM_QDRANT_INFERENCE_MODEL=bge-small-en
# Optional: PODIUM_QDRANT_GRPC_PORT is reserved and not read; leave unset.


# =============================================================================
# Embedding providers (independent of the vector backends above)
# =============================================================================
# You do NOT need any of these to test the vector backends. Set a provider's key
# only to run that provider's own embedding live test. Each model defaults;
# override only to pin a model.

# ---- OpenAI -----------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# PODIUM_OPENAI_MODEL=        # default text-embedding-3-small
# PODIUM_OPENAI_BASE_URL=     # default api.openai.com; set for a compatible endpoint
# PODIUM_OPENAI_ORG=          # set only if your account requires an org header

# ---- Cohere -----------------------------------------------------------------
# COHERE_API_KEY=
# PODIUM_COHERE_MODEL=        # default embed-v4

# ---- Voyage AI --------------------------------------------------------------
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=
# PODIUM_VOYAGE_MODEL=        # default voyage-3

# ---- Ollama (self-hosted; no account) ---------------------------------------
# PODIUM_OLLAMA_URL=          # default http://localhost:11434
# PODIUM_OLLAMA_MODEL=        # default nomic-embed-text


# =============================================================================
# Sigstore (manual signing validation; not part of make test-live-external)
# =============================================================================
# PODIUM_SIGSTORE_FULCIO_URL=https://fulcio.sigstage.dev
# PODIUM_SIGSTORE_REKOR_URL=https://rekor.sigstage.dev
# PODIUM_SIGSTORE_OIDC_TOKEN=
# PODIUM_SIGSTORE_TRUST_ROOT_PEM_FILE=
